- Engagement rate calculation
- Duplicate detection
- Automatic Telegram notifications
- Static workflow memory
- Batch processing
- JavaScript data processing
- Trend monitoring

---

## 🔄 Workflow

1. The workflow starts automatically on a scheduled interval.
2. A predefined list of YouTube niches is generated.
3. Videos published during the last 7 days are retrieved through the YouTube Data API.
4. Video IDs and metadata are extracted.
5. Previously processed videos are filtered out using workflow static storage.
6. Videos are grouped into batches for efficient API requests.
7. Detailed statistics are retrieved for every video.
8. Performance metrics are calculated, including:
   - Views
   - Likes
   - Comments
   - Views per hour
   - Engagement rate
   - Video age
9. Videos are evaluated by the outlier detection algorithm.
10. The best-performing videos are formatted into a report.
11. Results are automatically delivered to Telegram.

